nt than ever to engage in productive discussion, which begins with being informed about content that is still scarcely understood outside small industry and fan circles. Erotic Comics in Japan: An Introduction to Eromanga is the most comprehensive introduction in English to erotic comics in Japan, or eromanga. Divided into three parts, it provides a history of eroticism in Japanese comics and cartoons generally leading to the emergence of eromanga specifically, an overview of seven themes running across works with close analysis of outstanding examples and a window onto ongoing debates surrounding regulation and freedom of expression in Japan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aErotic comic books, strips, etczJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aErotic drawing. 0aErotic literature, Japanese. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aMedia Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh  aJapan, comics, sexuality.1 aBauwens-Sugimoto, Jessica.1 aGalbraith, Patrick.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978904855072240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048550722/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Co